amplitude

The  amplitude  attribute controls the amplitude of the gamma function of a component transfer element
when its <L=2X> type </L> attribute is  gamma  .

You can use this attribute with the following SVG elements:

-   <L=3J> <feFuncA> </L>
-   <L=3K> <feFuncB> </L>
-   <L=3L> <feFuncG> </L>
-   <L=3M> <feFuncR> </L>

<L=j#4>Usage notes</L><I=4>
  --------------- ----------
  Value           <number>
  Default value    1 
  Animatable      Yes
  --------------- ----------

<L=j#5>Specifications</L><I=5>
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Specification
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Filter Effects Module Level 1
  # element-attrdef-fecomponenttransfer-amplitude

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<L=j#6>See also</L><I=6>
-   <L=3B> <feComponentTransfer> </L>
