attributeName

The attributeName attribute indicates the name of the CSS property or attribute of the target element
that is going to be changed during an animation.

You can use this attribute with the following SVG elements:

-   <animate>
-   <animateTransform>
-   <set>

Example

    html,
    body,
    svg {
      height: 100%;
    }

```html

    <svg viewBox="0 0 250 250" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
      <rect x="50" y="50" width="100" height="100">
        <animate
          attributeType="XML"
          attributeName="y"
          from="0"
          to="50"
          dur="5s"
          repeatCount="indefinite" />
      </rect>
    </svg>
```

Usage notes

  --------------- --------
  Value           <name>
  Default value   None
  Animatable      No
  --------------- --------

<name>

    This value indicates the name of the CSS property or attribute of the target element to be animated.

Specifications

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Specification
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  SVG Animations Level 2
  # AttributeNameAttribute

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

See also

-   SVG animation with SMIL






