data-*

The  data-*  SVG attributes are called custom data attributes. They let SVG markup and its resulting DOM
share information that standard attributes can't, usually for scripting purposes. Their custom data are
available via the  SVGElement  interface of the element the attributes belong to, with the
 SVGElement.dataset  property.

The  *  can be replaced by any characters allowed in XML's rules for names , with the following
restrictions:

-   Can't start with  xml  .
-   No semicolons (  ;  ,  U+003A  ).
-   No capital  A  to  Z  letters.

Note: The  SVGElement.dataset  property is a  DOMStringMap  that provides the attribute  data-test-value 
via  SVGElement.dataset.testValue  . Hyphen characters (  -  ,  U+002D  ) are removed and the next letter
is capitalized, resulting in the camel case format.

You can use this attribute with any SVG element.

<L=H#4>Specifications</L><I=4>
