in2

The  in2  attribute identifies the second input for the given filter primitive. It works exactly like the
<L=1k> in </L> attribute.

You can use this attribute with the following SVG elements:

-   <L=3z> <feBlend> </L>
-   <L=3C> <feComposite> </L>
-   <L=3F> <feDisplacementMap> </L>

<L=1l#4>feBlend</L><I=4>
For <L=3z> <feBlend> </L> ,  in2  defines the second input image to the blending operation.

  --------------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Value            SourceGraphic  |  SourceAlpha  |  BackgroundImage  |  BackgroundAlpha  |  FillPaint  |  StrokePaint  |  <filter-primitive-reference> 
  Default value    SourceGraphic  for first filter primitive, otherwise result of previous filter primitive
  Animatable      Yes
  --------------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<L=1l#5>feComposite</L><I=5>
For <L=3C> <feComposite> </L> ,  in2  defines the second input image to the compositing operation.

  --------------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Value            SourceGraphic  |  SourceAlpha  |  BackgroundImage  |  BackgroundAlpha  |  FillPaint  |  StrokePaint  |  <filter-primitive-reference> 
  Default value    SourceGraphic  for first filter primitive, otherwise result of previous filter primitive
  Animatable      Yes
  --------------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<L=1l#6>feDisplacementMap</L><I=6>
For <L=3F> <feDisplacementMap> </L> ,  in2  defines the second input image, which is used to displace the
pixels in the image defined in the <L=1k> in </L> attribute.

  --------------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Value            SourceGraphic  |  SourceAlpha  |  BackgroundImage  |  BackgroundAlpha  |  FillPaint  |  StrokePaint  |  <filter-primitive-reference> 
  Default value    SourceGraphic  for first filter primitive, otherwise result of previous filter primitive
  Animatable      Yes
  --------------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<L=1l#7>Specifications</L><I=7>
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Specification
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Filter Effects Module Level 1
  # element-attrdef-fedisplacementmap-in2

  Filter Effects Module Level 1
  # element-attrdef-fecomposite-in2

  Filter Effects Module Level 1
  # element-attrdef-feblend-in2
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
